TY  - JOUR
T1  - Private International Debt with Risk of Repudiation
AU  - Jeske, Karsten
Y1  - 2006/06/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/503755
DO  - 10.1086/503755
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 576
EP  - 593
VL  - 114
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The risk of repudiation plays a central role in determining the size of international capital flows. In this paper I compare a centralized arrangement for international debt, where only governments borrow and lend internationally, with a decentralized arrangement, where individual borrowers have access to international capital markets. I show that a centralized setup allows more international risk sharing and higher welfare than a decentralized setup. That is, there is a positive role for government regulation of international borrowing.
AB  - The risk of repudiation plays a central role in determining the size of international capital flows. In this paper I compare a centralized arrangement for international debt, where only governments borrow and lend internationally, with a decentralized arrangement, where individual borrowers have access to international capital markets. I show that a centralized setup allows more international risk sharing and higher welfare than a decentralized setup. That is, there is a positive role for government regulation of international borrowing.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/503755
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/503755
Y2  - 2024/03/19
